original: Johnson, Lave Botvid, kyrkoherde, Siätiila, f. 313/12/94 i Öxabäck, ÄlVsb. 1., av pros(teni Birger J. o. Berta Ardeilil. — Stud:ex, i Halmstad 13, teol. fil. ex. 14, teol. kand. samt prakt. teol. prov 17, prästv. f. Gbgs stift 18. Mis-siv i Svenneby, Kville, Laholm, Grime-ton o. Sätila, kommin. i Askum 24, kyrkoh. i Sätila 33.
translated: Johnson, Lave Botvid, vicar, Sätila, b. December 31, 1894 in Öxabäck, Älvsborg County, son of the pastor Birger J. and Berta Ardeilil. He finished high school in Halmstad in 1913, obtained a Bachelor of Theology degree in 1914, passed the practical theological exam in 1917, and was ordained as a priest for the Gothenburg diocese in 1918. He worked as a missionary in Svenneby, Kville, Laholm, Grimeton, and Sätila and served as a curate in Askum in 1924. He became the vicar in Sätila in 1933. He married, but the name of his partner and the year of their marriage is unknown.
